00:13.528 --> 00:15.931
JOHNSON: <i>Previously on</i> Masters of Sex...

00:15.932 --> 00:17.200
I told them the truth.

00:17.201 --> 00:18.403
What did they say?

00:18.404 --> 00:21.241
They just packed their stuff and left.

00:21.242 --> 00:22.878
Why are you doing this?

00:22.879 --> 00:24.782
<i>Perhaps I should just
talk to your boss.</i>

00:24.783 --> 00:26.619
For some reason, he's
gotten it into his head

00:26.620 --> 00:28.189
that I don't pass muster.

00:28.190 --> 00:29.759
It can't be a coincidence
that it happened

00:29.760 --> 00:32.397
right after my fiancée
called off our wedding.

00:32.398 --> 00:34.769
The Clavermores have travelled
all the way from Philadelphia.

00:34.770 --> 00:36.906
Dr. Masters and Mrs. Johnson
are unreachable today.

00:36.907 --> 00:38.577
Why don't I begin your intake?

00:38.578 --> 00:40.379
NANCY: <i>Was Virginia
the boss in bed, too?</i>

00:40.380 --> 00:42.150
ART: <i>Nance, come on.</i>

00:42.151 --> 00:44.956
I vividly remember telling you
that you needed to be honest

00:44.957 --> 00:49.297
with your wife about what
did not happen between us.

00:49.298 --> 00:50.801
They've got the whole place wired.

00:50.802 --> 00:53.940
Honey, did you have a bad dream?

00:53.941 --> 00:56.446
<i>I don't think he even
saw you, thank God.</i>

00:56.447 --> 00:58.115
Why would it be so bad
if he did see me?

00:58.116 --> 01:00.319
There are reasons that we
shouldn't be together.

01:00.320 --> 01:02.725
Reasons that I am no
longer afraid to say.

01:02.726 --> 01:03.927
What is your position on dinner?

01:03.928 --> 01:05.464
My favorite meal of the day.

01:05.465 --> 01:07.233
I mean how would you like
to take me to dinner?

01:07.234 --> 01:09.405
The prosecution has sent
over a new witness list.

01:09.406 --> 01:11.409
There's a name on it I don't recognize.

01:11.410 --> 01:13.480
Works as a bellhop at the
Park Chancery Hotel.

01:13.481 --> 01:15.049
Park Chancery?

01:15.050 --> 01:16.753
<i>Yeah, they're going to
call him to testify</i>

01:16.754 --> 01:19.458
<i>Virginia Johnson and
I have been meeting</i>

01:19.459 --> 01:20.894
<i>at the Park Chancery.</i>

01:20.895 --> 01:22.665
I would be willing to discuss a plea.

01:22.666 --> 01:27.508
I know what you did, Bill,
and I know why you did it.

01:27.509 --> 01:31.082
Finally we are back where
we belong, together.

01:32.953 --> 01:35.958
<i>♪ sultry music ♪</i>

01:35.959 --> 01:40.969
<i>♪♪♪</i>

02:13.443 --> 02:16.243
- sync and corrections by Caio -
- www.addic7ed.com -

02:17.642 --> 02:20.647
<i>♪ soft music ♪</i>

02:20.648 --> 02:25.658
<i>♪♪♪</i>

02:38.718 --> 02:39.885
Virginia...

02:39.886 --> 02:41.522
I should have called first. I know.

02:41.523 --> 02:43.225
Did I leave something at the office?

02:43.226 --> 02:46.432
Did you...? Oh, no.

02:46.433 --> 02:49.672
I, uh, I have just
gotten some good news.

02:49.673 --> 02:53.245
And I wanted to share it
with you soon as I heard.

02:53.246 --> 02:54.882
May I come in?

02:54.883 --> 02:56.887
Um, sure.

03:02.164 --> 03:04.033
You have a cat.

03:04.034 --> 03:06.806
Yeah, Ernie.

03:06.807 --> 03:10.514
Well, I've, uh, I've
been calling him Ernie.

03:10.515 --> 03:13.051
I, uh, I recently found out

03:13.052 --> 03:16.425
he already has a name: Miss Julie.

03:16.426 --> 03:19.698
You know, they have apartments
that come already furnished.

03:19.699 --> 03:22.604
Oh, no, this was furnished.
It was quite cluttered.

03:22.605 --> 03:25.911
So I stacked everything up
and threw a cover on it.

03:25.912 --> 03:28.883
You know, I've tried
to simplify things.

03:28.884 --> 03:30.954
Well, you would be surprised
how little it takes

03:30.955 --> 03:32.356
to make a place feel like a home.

03:32.357 --> 03:34.260
Coffee table comes in handy.

03:34.261 --> 03:36.599
Maybe... sofa

03:36.600 --> 03:38.604
for when you have guests.

03:44.048 --> 03:47.053
Uh, you wanted to celebrate?

03:47.054 --> 03:50.493
Yes, uh, I just heard
from Arnold Ketterman

03:50.494 --> 03:52.263
at Little Brown.

03:52.264 --> 03:55.169
Uh, he wants to move ahead
with publishing the new book.

03:55.170 --> 03:57.106
Oh, wow, that is good news.

03:57.107 --> 03:58.476
It's terrific news.

03:58.477 --> 04:00.947
The book was as good
as dead a week ago.

04:00.948 --> 04:03.787
I suppose it was my trip to
New York made the difference.

04:07.729 --> 04:10.232
Do you have champagne glasses?

04:10.233 --> 04:11.969
Um, I don't know.

04:11.970 --> 04:13.707
Maybe there's some in the closet.

04:21.656 --> 04:24.496
Uh, well I think this may
be your best option.

04:27.167 --> 04:28.670
What about you?

04:28.671 --> 04:32.611
Oh, uh, after months of AA,

04:32.612 --> 04:36.819
um, drinking has begun
to lose its appeal.

04:36.820 --> 04:39.123
But don't let that stop you.

04:39.124 --> 04:41.094
In fact, uh, when you came in,

04:41.095 --> 04:44.033
I was just on my way out to a meeting.

04:44.034 --> 04:48.008
You're welcome to... to take the cup.

04:48.009 --> 04:51.314
You're still doing that? AA?

04:51.315 --> 04:52.985
Uh-huh.

04:52.986 --> 04:56.892
Sobriety is a journey,
not a destination.

04:56.893 --> 04:58.730
(KEYS JINGLE)

04:58.731 --> 05:03.674
<i>♪♪♪</i>

05:07.080 --> 05:10.420
(DOG BARKING)

05:10.421 --> 05:12.356
- Hey.
- LIBBY:  Oh, my God, Bill.

05:12.357 --> 05:13.860
You scared me half to death.

05:13.861 --> 05:15.630
Baxter and I thought
it was an intruder.

05:15.631 --> 05:18.368
Oh, I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

05:18.369 --> 05:19.772
Can I fix you a drink?

05:19.773 --> 05:21.207
Uh, I hope you're not here

05:21.208 --> 05:22.978
expecting a repeat
performance of last week.

05:22.979 --> 05:24.548
No, you made it very clear,

05:24.549 --> 05:27.386
uh, there'd be no
encores... in that regard.

05:27.387 --> 05:29.458
So I-I thought we could watch the, uh,

05:29.459 --> 05:31.327
<i>The Tonight Show</i> together.

05:31.328 --> 05:33.398
When was the last time we did that?

05:33.399 --> 05:36.472
Before we filed for divorce.

05:36.473 --> 05:38.910
Does the TV in your apartment not work?

05:38.911 --> 05:40.914
I-I had to get out of the apartment.

05:40.915 --> 05:43.251
I was feeling, you know...
(EXASPERATED SIGH)

05:43.252 --> 05:46.024
- ...claustrophobic.
- (CHUCKLES) You live alone.

05:46.025 --> 05:48.729
Well, that's just it, yeah.

05:48.730 --> 05:51.234
I mean, I, you know, I...

05:51.235 --> 05:55.042
I feel alone... (CHUCKLES) there.

05:55.043 --> 05:56.612
That's why I-I'm gonna ask Barton

05:56.613 --> 05:58.381
to come back to the clinic.

05:58.382 --> 06:00.987
You know, he's been such
a constant in my life.

06:00.988 --> 06:02.524
Like family.

06:02.525 --> 06:07.534
And since our family is
no longer what it was,

06:07.535 --> 06:09.805
and, uh,

06:09.806 --> 06:11.642
Virginia and I are... are
no longer what we were...

06:11.643 --> 06:14.648
Might I suggest that
you consider dating.

06:14.649 --> 06:16.819
(SCOFFS) Dating? Libby.

06:16.820 --> 06:19.725
Why not? I am.

06:19.726 --> 06:21.595
Who?

06:21.596 --> 06:24.935
Bram Keller.

06:24.936 --> 06:26.939
Bram Keller...

06:26.940 --> 06:28.108
...asked you out?

06:28.109 --> 06:30.245
My... my defense attorney, Bram Keller?

06:30.246 --> 06:33.686
Well, actually, I asked him.

06:33.687 --> 06:34.755
I hope it isn't awkward.

06:34.756 --> 06:37.694
Awk... no. Why...

06:37.695 --> 06:38.796
why would it be awkward?

06:38.797 --> 06:40.900
It's just a date, Bill.

06:40.901 --> 06:43.639
And I think it is a
healthy next step for me,

06:43.640 --> 06:47.414
as it would be for you.

06:47.415 --> 06:50.085
"Friar Bill"... it does
have a certain ring to it.

06:50.086 --> 06:51.589
All that's missing from his apartment

06:51.590 --> 06:54.093
is a monk's robe and a hair shirt.

06:54.094 --> 06:56.832
I do appreciate the
drink. And the company.

06:56.833 --> 06:59.270
Better than going home.

06:59.271 --> 07:01.542
Plus you cleared things up with Nancy.

07:01.543 --> 07:03.211
I'm not one to hold a grudge.

07:03.212 --> 07:04.514
Especially against a colleague.

07:04.515 --> 07:07.954
How is it possible Bill
Masters has a cat?

07:07.955 --> 07:09.558
(CHUCKLES)

07:09.559 --> 07:13.131
Honestly, I-I find that man
completely inscrutable.

07:13.132 --> 07:16.204
And I have always understood him,

07:16.205 --> 07:17.874
but these past few months, he's been...

07:17.875 --> 07:19.210
Well, he's in the middle of a divorce.

07:19.211 --> 07:20.713
That doesn't explain this.

07:20.714 --> 07:23.486
Come on. Erratic,
uncharacteristic behavior,

07:23.487 --> 07:25.389
isolating himself from those
with whom he was once close.

07:25.390 --> 07:27.761
Yes, traditionally those
would be symptoms

07:27.762 --> 07:29.498
of a man coming out of a long marriage,

07:29.499 --> 07:31.802
but every marriage is different.

07:31.803 --> 07:34.508
For example, I nearly sent
out celebration notices

07:34.509 --> 07:36.110
when I got divorced.

07:36.111 --> 07:37.947
Each time.

07:37.948 --> 07:40.486
But even an unfulfilling
marriage can provide

07:40.487 --> 07:43.426
a certain kind of, uh, stability.

07:43.427 --> 07:45.663
At Kinsey, we found men
typically took divorce

07:45.664 --> 07:47.434
much harder than women.

07:47.435 --> 07:50.873
And women were able to establish
new routines, create new lives.

07:50.874 --> 07:55.382
Whereas husbands, used to
having their laundry pressed,

07:55.383 --> 07:56.885
dinners cooked, they
floundered without wives.

07:56.886 --> 07:58.723
And yet here you are,

07:58.724 --> 08:00.727
eating Chinese food at the office

08:00.728 --> 08:03.899
while your wife is...
where is Nancy tonight?

08:03.900 --> 08:05.436
Thank you for reminding me.

08:05.437 --> 08:07.172
Here I'd gone a whole three minutes

08:07.173 --> 08:09.310
without thinking of Nancy's "dinner"

08:09.311 --> 08:13.151
with her old college "friend," Bruce.

08:13.152 --> 08:15.088
My point is,

08:15.089 --> 08:18.629
Bill's relationship that most
resembled a true marriage

08:18.630 --> 08:20.298
was with me.

08:20.299 --> 08:22.637
I was his work wife.

08:22.638 --> 08:24.808
And since work was always his life...

08:24.809 --> 08:27.814
But now he's remarrying, thanks to you.

08:27.815 --> 08:31.387
My wife. His new work wife.

08:31.388 --> 08:33.057
He keeps telling Nancy

08:33.058 --> 08:35.462
he wants her involved in everything.

08:35.464 --> 08:38.470
Every aspect of the clinic.

08:40.874 --> 08:42.876
(KEYS JINGLE)

08:42.878 --> 08:45.416
<i>♪♪♪</i>

08:45.417 --> 08:46.418
Bob?

08:46.419 --> 08:48.923
<i>♪♪♪</i>

08:48.924 --> 08:51.930
Hey, Bob. Wake up.

08:54.769 --> 08:57.775
Just the man I wanted to see.

09:00.179 --> 09:01.281
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

09:03.319 --> 09:05.490
BOB: It's a beautiful place you have!

09:05.491 --> 09:08.127
Must be 800 square feet!

09:08.128 --> 09:09.898
Can you just keep your
voice down a little, Bob?

09:09.899 --> 09:11.835
It's 12:30 in the morning.

09:11.836 --> 09:15.141
Do you even know how much
this kind of square footage

09:15.142 --> 09:17.346
would go for in Manhattan? (CHUCKLES)

09:17.347 --> 09:18.983
I'll have you coffee in a minute.

09:18.984 --> 09:21.421
Your speech. Let's talk
about your speech.

09:21.422 --> 09:22.690
My speech?

09:22.691 --> 09:24.494
At... at the courthouse last week.

09:24.495 --> 09:29.236
"No two human beings would
paint the same painting."

09:29.237 --> 09:31.575
(CHUCKLES) How true is that?

09:31.576 --> 09:34.514
On a scale of one to ten,
ten being the truest,

09:34.515 --> 09:35.950
how true is that?

09:35.951 --> 09:38.087
I say 12, off the scale.

09:38.088 --> 09:39.089
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

09:39.090 --> 09:40.258
You're very kind.

09:40.259 --> 09:42.396
"A being's sexual response

09:42.397 --> 09:44.133
isn't formed on the assembly line.

09:44.134 --> 09:47.139
There is no shape that it must take."

09:47.140 --> 09:48.809
You memorized it?

09:48.810 --> 09:50.813
And I've decided we're going
to use it as the forward

09:50.814 --> 09:53.652
to the... your book.

09:53.653 --> 09:55.255
Because it's so true, what you said.

09:55.256 --> 09:59.063
"There is no norm. There
is only deviation."

09:59.064 --> 10:00.332
Did you mean that?

10:00.333 --> 10:02.302
Is there someone I
should be calling, Bob?

10:02.303 --> 10:04.841
Let them know where you are?

10:04.842 --> 10:07.447
I don't know where I am.

10:07.448 --> 10:08.916
Well, you're in St. Louis.

10:08.917 --> 10:10.251
No, no. (CHUCKLES)

10:10.252 --> 10:11.421
No, that's not what I mean.

10:11.422 --> 10:14.861
I mean... (CHUCKLES)

10:14.862 --> 10:17.635
...it sounds so stupid, but...

10:19.872 --> 10:22.009
...I'm lost.

10:22.010 --> 10:24.113
I'm almost 40 years old

10:24.114 --> 10:28.956
and about to lose the only shot
I'll ever have at a family.

10:28.957 --> 10:30.660
She left me once.

10:30.661 --> 10:33.398
If she leaves me again,
it's... it's for good.

10:33.399 --> 10:34.834
She being?

10:34.835 --> 10:37.573
Cherlyn. My fiancée.

10:37.574 --> 10:41.147
She's the reason I'm here.

10:41.148 --> 10:43.752
I need you to fix me, Doc.

10:43.753 --> 10:48.227
I need you to see me,
see us, as patients.

10:48.228 --> 10:52.335
So, can... can you fit us in tomorrow?

10:52.336 --> 10:55.677
(TEA KETTLE WHISTLING)

10:59.084 --> 11:00.886
(HELEN EXHALES DEEPLY)

11:00.887 --> 11:02.657
(DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE)

11:02.658 --> 11:05.328
- Hey.
- Hey.

11:05.329 --> 11:07.065
Bad night?

11:07.066 --> 11:09.136
- I got a couple hours sleep.
- Mm.

11:09.137 --> 11:10.506
She was kicking a lot.

11:10.507 --> 11:12.677
He's impatient.

11:12.678 --> 11:14.179
She's strong-willed.

11:14.180 --> 11:17.186
Mm. He's just like his mother.

11:21.662 --> 11:23.331
(GROANS SOFTLY)

11:23.332 --> 11:25.770
I had a dream my folks were here again.

11:25.771 --> 11:27.774
Oh, honey, I'm so sorry.

11:27.775 --> 11:29.711
No, it wasn't a sad dream this time.

11:29.712 --> 11:32.015
Well, who cried? 'Cause someone
always ends up crying.

11:32.016 --> 11:34.721
No one. Not even me.

11:34.722 --> 11:38.529
I mean, they still rejected me,

11:38.530 --> 11:41.768
rejected us, but when they left,

11:41.769 --> 11:45.910
I waved good-bye and
they blew me a kiss.

11:45.911 --> 11:48.982
And it was really...
it was really okay.

11:48.983 --> 11:51.320
And I wasn't sad anymore.

11:51.321 --> 11:53.659
'Cause when I turned around,
you and our baby girl

11:53.660 --> 11:55.161
were standing there.

11:55.162 --> 11:58.267
That's when I knew how happy I was.

11:58.268 --> 12:01.408
How happy we're gonna be.

12:01.409 --> 12:03.512
Just me, you, and Sweetpea.

12:03.513 --> 12:05.850
A family.

12:05.851 --> 12:09.022
Aren't we lucky?

12:09.023 --> 12:10.593
A whole dream,

12:10.594 --> 12:12.630
and that baby never once complained

12:12.631 --> 12:14.635
that he's tired of
being called a "she"?

12:19.110 --> 12:22.617
No, not once.

12:22.618 --> 12:26.123
But you'll be able to take
it up with her very shortly.

12:26.124 --> 12:29.765
Hey, how shortly?

12:31.669 --> 12:33.639
NANCY: You were out late.

12:33.640 --> 12:35.943
I got bogged down at the office.

12:35.944 --> 12:37.914
I started to think maybe you
were spending the night

12:37.915 --> 12:40.184
somewhere else.

12:40.185 --> 12:43.090
How's Bruce?

12:43.091 --> 12:46.196
He made tenure, so...

12:46.197 --> 12:48.200
...that was mostly dinner conversation.

12:48.201 --> 12:51.307
And he came bearing gifts.

12:51.308 --> 12:52.843
Uh, this is for me?

12:52.844 --> 12:56.451
(CHUCKLES) Perfect color for your eyes.

12:56.452 --> 12:57.954
Julia must have picked it out

12:57.955 --> 13:01.260
since Bruce has zero fashion sense.

13:01.261 --> 13:03.465
How thoughtful.

13:03.466 --> 13:05.168
I hope you told him I'm
sorry I missed him.

13:05.169 --> 13:06.838
Well, he doesn't fly
out until tomorrow,

13:06.839 --> 13:10.612
so he wants to take the two
of us out to dinner tonight.

13:10.613 --> 13:12.617
He's dying to catch up with you.

13:15.022 --> 13:17.526
Hmm.

13:17.527 --> 13:19.764
I can have the bedspread,
stemware, and china delivered.

13:19.765 --> 13:22.268
And maybe rush-delivered, since
it sounds like Dr. Masters

13:22.269 --> 13:24.640
is eating all of his meals
from an antique teacup.

13:24.641 --> 13:26.711
Yes, I think if we wait for Dr. Masters

13:26.712 --> 13:28.014
to order all of this for himself...

13:28.015 --> 13:30.486
He's constitutionally incapable.

13:30.487 --> 13:31.855
He's straight. (CHUCKLES)

13:31.856 --> 13:33.391
Cases for review.

13:33.392 --> 13:37.833
And is Dr. Masters' color
palette warm or cool?

13:37.834 --> 13:39.470
Color palette?

13:39.471 --> 13:41.875
It's fine. I'll be the wife.

13:41.876 --> 13:46.886
<i>♪♪♪</i>

13:51.529 --> 13:53.665
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

13:53.666 --> 13:55.101
Oh, I have never been so happy

13:55.102 --> 13:56.771
to see someone in my entire life.

13:56.772 --> 13:58.909
Get over here. Give me a hug.

13:58.910 --> 14:00.579
(CHUCKLES)

14:00.580 --> 14:01.981
(EXHALES DEEPLY) God, what a mess.

14:01.982 --> 14:03.452
Can I help you unpack?

14:03.453 --> 14:07.192
Well, you can keep me
company while I do.

14:07.193 --> 14:08.562
You look well, honey.

14:08.563 --> 14:11.166
And you look friendly, which will be

14:11.167 --> 14:13.204
a-a welcome change around here.

14:13.205 --> 14:14.874
Well, Bill would be the first to admit

14:14.875 --> 14:17.378
he doesn't have the most
genial bedside manner.

14:17.379 --> 14:19.750
Okay, it's not that. It's the...

14:19.751 --> 14:21.554
No, no, I'm not gonna complain.

14:21.555 --> 14:23.592
Not... not on your first day back.

14:23.593 --> 14:26.230
Oh.

14:26.231 --> 14:29.670
Okay, so...

14:29.671 --> 14:31.441
...when Dr. Masters first hired me,

14:31.442 --> 14:34.714
I was told that I was being
brought on as his partner.

14:34.715 --> 14:36.951
But he and Virginia,
they always find a way

14:36.952 --> 14:38.254
to go back to working together,

14:38.255 --> 14:40.124
so Art and I, we're always left out.

14:40.125 --> 14:42.095
Well, I'm sure it's not intentional.

14:42.096 --> 14:43.865
Do you know they tape everything?

14:43.866 --> 14:46.036
Oh, they've been taping
sessions for years.

14:46.037 --> 14:47.205
For archival purposes.

14:47.206 --> 14:48.642
Oh, I'm not talking about that.

14:48.643 --> 14:50.412
I'm talking about taping the staff.

14:50.413 --> 14:53.117
Recording private conversations.

14:53.118 --> 14:56.223
Look, I am so grateful you
recommended me for this job,

14:56.224 --> 14:59.664
b-but I also... I-I can't help feeling

14:59.665 --> 15:01.901
like there's something strange
going on between them.

15:01.902 --> 15:03.772
Bill and Virginia have
been working together

15:03.773 --> 15:05.174
for over a decade.

15:05.175 --> 15:07.880
You and Art have been here for a month.

15:07.881 --> 15:09.684
Give it some time.

15:09.685 --> 15:10.852
You'll find your way.

15:10.853 --> 15:12.088
(KNOCKING, DOOR OPENS)

15:12.089 --> 15:13.892
Dr. Scully? Betty just telephoned.

15:13.893 --> 15:15.361
She and Helen are on their
way to the hospital.

15:15.362 --> 15:16.396
She says it's time.

15:16.397 --> 15:18.902
Oh. Excuse me.

15:18.903 --> 15:20.973
I will tell Mr. Spleeb when
he gets back from court.

15:20.974 --> 15:22.911
Right. Thank you.

15:25.249 --> 15:27.118
When I said dinner,

15:27.119 --> 15:28.888
I wasn't imagining the
early bird special.

15:28.889 --> 15:30.826
Actually, I've come hat in hand.

15:30.827 --> 15:32.563
I need to reschedule for tonight.

15:32.564 --> 15:34.332
I've got a last-minute
work dinner, but...

15:34.333 --> 15:35.802
Don't say another word.

15:35.803 --> 15:39.443
I am very familiar with
"last-minute work dinners."

15:39.444 --> 15:41.648
One of Bill's old standbys.

15:41.649 --> 15:43.818
Not as common as "late
night at the office,"

15:43.819 --> 15:45.789
but easier to refute
than "stuck in traffic."

15:45.790 --> 15:47.258
Believe me, I've used them all,

15:47.259 --> 15:48.327
but this time I mean it.

15:48.328 --> 15:49.964
It's a client and his wife,

15:49.965 --> 15:51.534
and normally I'd be thrilled
to have you on my arm...

15:51.535 --> 15:53.170
Except for some strange reason,

15:53.171 --> 15:54.807
you're prevented from including me.

15:54.808 --> 15:55.809
Wait, let me guess.

15:55.810 --> 15:57.880
They are... communists.

15:57.881 --> 15:59.517
No, they're lepers.

15:59.518 --> 16:01.954
They're nudists.

16:01.955 --> 16:04.292
Oh, well, points for originality.

16:04.293 --> 16:07.332
Libby, I care about this first date.

16:07.333 --> 16:08.802
I don't want it to be a steak dinner

16:08.803 --> 16:12.409
surrounded by nude people.

16:12.410 --> 16:14.279
And why not?

16:14.280 --> 16:17.653
- Because I'm such a prude.
- (SCOFFS) No.

16:17.654 --> 16:19.155
Because I see a little bare skin

16:19.156 --> 16:21.326
and I have to retire
to my fainting couch.

16:21.327 --> 16:23.965
- That's not fair.
- Smelling salts at the ready.

16:23.966 --> 16:25.202
(CHUCKLES)

16:27.507 --> 16:29.977
Fine. I'll pick you up at 5:30.

16:29.978 --> 16:32.516
<i>♪ upbeat music ♪</i>

16:32.517 --> 16:35.655
Although, if you've never
spent time around nudists,

16:35.656 --> 16:38.327
I'd suggest bringing
those smelling salts,

16:38.328 --> 16:40.966
just in case.

16:40.967 --> 16:44.473
<i>♪♪♪</i>

16:44.474 --> 16:47.345
How do you think Dr. Masters
feels about demitasse?

16:47.346 --> 16:49.750
Guy, why is the initial interview

16:49.751 --> 16:52.388
for the Clavermores already completed?

16:52.389 --> 16:55.227
Filled out by Art and Nancy?

16:55.228 --> 16:57.666
Uh, right.

16:57.667 --> 16:59.169
Mr. and Mrs. Monopoly, I remember them.

16:59.170 --> 17:00.672
There was a schedule snafu.

17:00.673 --> 17:02.676
They came in while you and
Dr. Masters were in court.

17:02.677 --> 17:04.512
Well, then you should
have rescheduled them,

17:04.513 --> 17:06.851
not pawned them off on other doctors.

17:06.852 --> 17:09.490
I think "pawned off" is a strong term.

17:09.491 --> 17:11.394
Plus, it was Dr. Leveau's idea.

17:14.233 --> 17:18.575
Well, then let's go
look at the calendar

17:18.576 --> 17:20.712
in case Dr. Leveau has generously taken

17:20.713 --> 17:22.816
other cases off our hands.

17:22.817 --> 17:24.553
And how did you two meet?

17:24.554 --> 17:26.424
It was a blind date.

17:26.425 --> 17:29.095
Yeah, we both agreed we
would carry umbrellas

17:29.096 --> 17:30.832
so we would recognize each other.

17:30.833 --> 17:32.235
Then it started raining.

17:32.236 --> 17:34.272
There wasn't a person on that block

17:34.273 --> 17:36.911
without an umbrella.

17:36.912 --> 17:38.615
Guy, why is Nancy sitting in

17:38.616 --> 17:41.787
on a book meeting with Little Brown?

17:41.788 --> 17:43.223
It's not a book meeting.

17:43.224 --> 17:45.261
Then why is Bob Drag in there?

17:45.262 --> 17:49.035
I can't tell you, it's confidential.

17:49.036 --> 17:50.606
(WHISPERS) He's impotent.

17:54.280 --> 17:57.452
Uh, Miss Green, Bob
mentioned that you recently

17:57.453 --> 17:58.821
broke off your engagement.

17:58.822 --> 18:02.361
Only for a few weeks. It
was a hiatus, really.

18:02.362 --> 18:03.865
Was there a precipitating incident?

18:03.866 --> 18:06.604
Not really, no.

18:06.605 --> 18:09.075
Miss Green?

18:09.076 --> 18:13.350
Did you feel there was a
precipitating incident?

18:13.351 --> 18:18.360
Uh, well, we hadn't
made love in months.

18:18.361 --> 18:21.299
Because of his...

18:21.300 --> 18:22.869
Impotence.

18:22.870 --> 18:25.575
But as I explained to
Cherlyn, luckily for us,

18:25.576 --> 18:29.382
I happen to know the world's
foremost experts on the subject.

18:29.383 --> 18:31.219
We're here to sort this out,

18:31.220 --> 18:34.058
so we can marry, have children.

18:34.059 --> 18:38.635
The time apart, it
renewed our commitment.

18:38.636 --> 18:40.472
Well, you seem a lot more hopeful, Bob,

18:40.473 --> 18:42.341
than when I spoke to you last night.

18:42.342 --> 18:44.513
CHERLYN: Last night?

18:44.514 --> 18:48.086
I thought you were out at a
Little Brown function all night.

18:48.087 --> 18:51.093
I was. He just means we spoke by phone.

18:55.703 --> 18:57.439
Three centimeters dilated.

18:57.440 --> 18:59.543
Oh, that's good, right?

18:59.544 --> 19:01.312
That's right where we want you to be.

19:01.313 --> 19:02.616
Uh, what about the blood?

19:02.617 --> 19:04.620
There was a lot of blood
when her water broke.

19:04.621 --> 19:08.160
Oh, it's perfectly normal to see
some spotting at this point.

19:08.161 --> 19:11.066
You told the nurses you were
concerned about your vision.

19:11.067 --> 19:13.738
Oh, yeah, well, I was seeing spots

19:13.739 --> 19:15.775
and my head's been pounding.

19:15.776 --> 19:17.946
Mm, I suspect that has to do
with your blood pressure.

19:17.947 --> 19:20.852
It's within normal range, but
we'll keep an eye on it.

19:20.853 --> 19:25.094
Now the baby is still
breech, so at this point,

19:25.095 --> 19:26.697
there's a 50/50 chance

19:26.698 --> 19:29.770
we'll need to perform a Caesarean.

19:29.771 --> 19:32.174
Well, Caesareans are on the rise.

19:32.175 --> 19:34.480
I read it in <i>Woman's Day.</i>

19:34.481 --> 19:36.282
Now we're talking about surgery?

19:36.283 --> 19:39.623
Routine surgery. She'll
be awake, comfortable.

19:39.624 --> 19:42.896
The only difference is a
slightly longer recovery.

19:42.897 --> 19:44.466
I'm gonna take you in now, Helen.

19:44.467 --> 19:46.971
Uh, Betty, the nurse will
show you to the waiting room.

19:46.972 --> 19:48.306
Oh, I-I'm not going
to the waiting room.

19:48.307 --> 19:49.643
I'm staying with her.

19:49.644 --> 19:50.678
Oh, yeah, she's staying with me.

19:50.679 --> 19:52.248
It's hospital policy.

19:52.249 --> 19:56.055
Not even husbands are allowed
in the delivery room.

19:56.056 --> 19:58.694
We'll get you in here as
soon as the baby comes.

19:58.695 --> 20:00.063
I promise.

20:00.064 --> 20:03.069
<i>♪ soft music ♪</i>

20:03.070 --> 20:04.372
<i>♪♪♪</i>

20:04.373 --> 20:07.913
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

20:07.914 --> 20:12.087
Sweetpea and I have
everything under control.

20:12.088 --> 20:16.797
<i>♪♪♪</i>

20:16.798 --> 20:18.467
JOHNSON: I'm just a bit confused

20:18.468 --> 20:20.438
as to why I wasn't brought in on this.

20:20.439 --> 20:21.807
A standard impotence case?

20:21.808 --> 20:24.546
A case involving the
publisher of our book is,

20:24.547 --> 20:26.417
by definition, non-standard.

20:26.418 --> 20:29.088
I meant the facts of the case
are relatively straightforward.

20:29.089 --> 20:33.230
Although I did find Bob
at my door last night,

20:33.231 --> 20:36.002
passed out, smelling like a distillery.

20:36.003 --> 20:38.741
Then he shows up here today
acting as if it never happened.

20:38.742 --> 20:41.012
That was my experience
with him in New York.

20:41.013 --> 20:43.016
One moment, he's this
buttoned-up professional.

20:43.017 --> 20:45.187
The next, he's groping me
in front of his colleagues.

20:45.188 --> 20:46.957
I don't know how well-founded they are,

20:46.958 --> 20:50.632
but the rumors around his office
are that he's a homosexual,

20:50.633 --> 20:52.334
and that's why his
engagement was broken off.

20:52.335 --> 20:54.305
He did go on last night
about the speech

20:54.306 --> 20:58.113
I made at the courthouse about
our embrace of deviancy.

20:58.114 --> 21:01.720
I-I did not sense any indication
of homosexual tendencies.

21:01.721 --> 21:03.658
And that's not your fault.

21:03.659 --> 21:05.294
Hey, you're still new to this work.

21:05.295 --> 21:08.333
What you'll learn is how to
pay attention to details.

21:08.334 --> 21:10.672
Well, details are what the
intake process is for,

21:10.673 --> 21:12.241
and we've yet to begin that.

21:12.242 --> 21:14.913
Of course, but given the sensitivity

21:14.914 --> 21:16.617
of this particular case,

21:16.618 --> 21:19.188
it makes most sense for us to
conduct the intake ourselves.

21:19.189 --> 21:22.862
Well, Nancy is perfectly capable
of conducting an intake.

21:22.863 --> 21:24.265
Oh, I'm sure she is.

21:24.266 --> 21:26.437
Oh, yes, she and Art
did an excellent job

21:26.438 --> 21:29.009
on the interview with the
Clavermores in our absence.

21:31.213 --> 21:33.651
You and Art took the Clavermores?

21:33.652 --> 21:35.220
They'd come all the way
from Philadelphia.

21:35.221 --> 21:37.726
Typically, the Clavermores
are the types of patients

21:37.727 --> 21:39.696
that we cultivate as donors.

21:39.697 --> 21:41.199
Well, after being on the
wait list for months,

21:41.200 --> 21:42.702
were we supposed to turn them away?

21:42.703 --> 21:45.742
No, just reschedule them.

21:45.743 --> 21:49.683
Unless you disagree, Bill.

21:49.684 --> 21:52.055
You should have consulted
with us before seeing them.

21:53.759 --> 21:55.595
I need to think about this,

21:55.596 --> 22:00.037
how to handle the Clavermores
from here on out.

22:00.038 --> 22:02.442
Nancy, could you give us a moment?

22:02.443 --> 22:04.045
<i>♪♪♪</i>

22:04.046 --> 22:05.982
(WHISPERS) Yeah.

22:05.983 --> 22:10.558
<i>♪♪♪</i>

22:10.559 --> 22:12.796
Anyway, I think that we
should double-team Drag.

22:12.797 --> 22:14.365
If we're right, and he is a homosexual,

22:14.366 --> 22:16.169
I'm sure between the two of us...

22:16.170 --> 22:18.474
Virginia, we can't keep yanking
Nancy off these cases.

22:18.475 --> 22:20.243
I'm not saying every case.

22:20.244 --> 22:21.980
The entire reason for
bringing Nancy and Art

22:21.981 --> 22:24.085
into the clinic was to help.

22:24.086 --> 22:26.924
Yes, but just like in
in the Bucksey case,

22:26.925 --> 22:29.095
there are certain instances
where it's much more effective

22:29.096 --> 22:31.500
for us to work together.

22:31.501 --> 22:34.406
Drag showed up at your door
in a very vulnerable state.

22:34.407 --> 22:36.410
He was open with you.

22:36.411 --> 22:39.014
But he was also open
with me in New York.

22:39.015 --> 22:42.121
<i>♪♪♪</i>

22:42.122 --> 22:44.024
I really believe that

22:44.025 --> 22:47.465
together we can coax
the truth out of him.

22:47.466 --> 22:52.476
<i>♪♪♪</i>

22:58.488 --> 23:02.261
Virginia?

23:02.262 --> 23:03.497
- Virginia?
- Yes?

23:03.498 --> 23:05.066
I'd like to have a word with you.

23:05.067 --> 23:07.070
This is really not the
appropriate time or place

23:07.071 --> 23:08.273
for a discussion.

23:08.274 --> 23:10.277
I, uh, I just need some clarification.

23:10.278 --> 23:12.282
(TOILET FLUSHES)

23:13.919 --> 23:16.389
Hey. What exactly was
I hired to do here?

23:16.390 --> 23:19.094
If you are going to constantly
remove me from my own cases,

23:19.095 --> 23:20.932
then what... what is my
role at this practice?

23:20.933 --> 23:25.575
Your role is to support Dr.
Masters as his partner.

23:25.576 --> 23:26.877
Well, except when you're his partner.

23:26.878 --> 23:28.614
In some instances, yes.

23:28.615 --> 23:30.751
- And who determines that?
- I do.

23:30.752 --> 23:32.655
Dr. Masters does.

23:32.656 --> 23:35.327
I'm sorry, Nancy, have you ever
run a business of your own?

23:35.328 --> 23:38.601
Ever built a practice from nothing?

23:38.602 --> 23:40.905
I wouldn't want to burden
you with the details,

23:40.906 --> 23:42.809
like securing research space...

23:42.810 --> 23:45.180
You didn't do that.

23:45.181 --> 23:48.954
Dr. Masters told me he
secured this space.

23:48.955 --> 23:52.829
Well, aside from that
technicality which, frankly,

23:52.830 --> 23:55.333
is debatable, you need to understand

23:55.334 --> 23:57.639
that there are many
factors that we weigh

23:57.640 --> 23:59.041
in every decision that we make here.

23:59.042 --> 24:00.978
Although the main factor
with me, for you,

24:00.979 --> 24:04.385
is that I am a woman.

24:04.386 --> 24:06.456
I'm not sure I know what you mean.

24:06.457 --> 24:07.992
You are competing with me.

24:07.993 --> 24:11.767
It's an understandable, if
disappointing reaction.

24:11.768 --> 24:13.570
Women get such a small
slice of the pie,

24:13.571 --> 24:14.773
they tend to fight over it,

24:14.774 --> 24:16.410
rather than make the slice bigger.

24:16.411 --> 24:19.081
- Or share.
- First of all, I hate pie.

24:19.082 --> 24:20.584
Secondly, you're speaking to a woman

24:20.585 --> 24:22.922
who has spent the last 12 years

24:22.923 --> 24:25.193
bringing women out of the Dark Ages.

24:25.194 --> 24:27.832
There's no greater advocate for women.

24:27.833 --> 24:30.705
In theory. This is practice.

24:30.706 --> 24:32.374
Look, I respect everything
you've accomplished.

24:32.375 --> 24:33.711
It's why I'm here.

24:33.712 --> 24:35.648
I just want to know where I stand.

24:35.649 --> 24:37.653
Wherever we tell you to.

24:43.698 --> 24:45.568
Knowing you as we do, Bob,

24:45.569 --> 24:49.409
it's clear to us both that you
deeply love your fiancée.

24:49.410 --> 24:53.149
I do, which is why this
impotence is so...

24:53.150 --> 24:55.688
(CHUCKLES)

24:55.689 --> 25:00.263
So, when did the impotence first
manifest itself with Miss Green?

25:00.264 --> 25:02.334
It really only started the
last couple of months.

25:02.335 --> 25:04.304
Any idea what brought it on?

25:04.305 --> 25:07.645
Stress? You saw what things
were like at Little Brown.

25:07.646 --> 25:10.150
Yes, that is one busy office.

25:10.151 --> 25:11.720
Although, stress is
only one of the many

25:11.721 --> 25:13.791
possible causes of impotence.

25:13.792 --> 25:16.663
Were there any episodes
with previous partners?

25:16.664 --> 25:18.199
Never.

25:18.200 --> 25:21.406
And your previous partners,
how many have there been?

25:21.407 --> 25:23.977
I know, a gentleman doesn't count.

25:23.978 --> 25:25.915
And you're not the type
to notch the bedpost.

25:25.916 --> 25:27.852
(CHUCKLES) Hardly.

25:27.853 --> 25:29.722
Uh, three or four, maybe.

25:29.723 --> 25:32.027
Three or four?

25:32.028 --> 25:35.066
You can't be certain
of the exact amount?

25:35.067 --> 25:37.204
It may be five.

25:37.205 --> 25:41.178
Actually, yes, I have been
sexually with five women.

25:41.179 --> 25:42.949
And the men that you've been with,

25:42.950 --> 25:44.385
how many were there?

25:48.461 --> 25:50.931
It's a standard question.

25:50.932 --> 25:53.236
Have you had sexual
experiences with men?

25:53.237 --> 25:55.407
Well, the answer is no.

25:55.408 --> 25:56.644
Obviously.

25:58.481 --> 26:01.653
Uh, men, no.

26:01.654 --> 26:03.322
Boys, perhaps?

26:03.323 --> 26:07.598
I mean when you were also a boy.

26:07.599 --> 26:09.669
Anything you discuss in this room...

26:09.670 --> 26:12.608
Remains strictly confidential.

26:12.609 --> 26:15.548
I have nothing to hide.

26:15.549 --> 26:18.019
And that...

26:18.020 --> 26:21.459
...that boy...

26:21.460 --> 26:23.697
...one boy. Once.

26:23.698 --> 26:25.534
When I had just turned 16.

26:25.535 --> 26:26.870
He was a year ahead of me.

26:26.871 --> 26:28.105
He was your classmate.

26:28.106 --> 26:29.943
At boarding school.

26:29.944 --> 26:31.479
It wasn't even sexual.

26:31.480 --> 26:34.318
Not really. Just... games.

26:34.319 --> 26:35.654
We were playing.

26:35.655 --> 26:37.324
And how many times did you engage...

26:37.325 --> 26:38.794
Like I said, a couple times.

26:38.795 --> 26:40.664
MASTERS: Did you have feelings for him?

26:40.665 --> 26:42.802
Feelings? What do feelings
mean when you're 16?

26:42.803 --> 26:45.474
Oh, they can mean a great deal.

26:45.475 --> 26:46.810
Let's talk about the others.

26:46.811 --> 26:50.016
There are no others. It
was just the one boy.

26:50.017 --> 26:52.455
He graduated the next year.
I never saw him again.

26:52.456 --> 26:53.490
But you still think about it.

26:53.491 --> 26:54.792
No.

26:54.793 --> 26:56.863
Well, from time to time.

26:56.864 --> 26:58.332
When you're with your fiancée?

26:58.333 --> 26:59.502
Not if I can help it.

26:59.503 --> 27:01.673
Does it help you to achieve erection?

27:01.674 --> 27:03.443
No.

27:03.444 --> 27:05.714
Y... yes. (EXHALES SHARPLY)

27:05.715 --> 27:07.384
I don't know.

27:07.385 --> 27:09.287
So, just sometimes you find

27:09.288 --> 27:13.062
the memory of this boy arousing.

27:13.063 --> 27:16.836
I find it nauseating.

27:16.837 --> 27:18.807
And sometimes arousing.

27:18.808 --> 27:22.516
But mostly, I find it
shameful and abhorrent.

27:25.455 --> 27:27.525
We would recommend, Bob,

27:27.526 --> 27:30.029
before beginning any kind
of sexual therapy...

27:30.030 --> 27:32.133
That you speak with a psychiatrist.

27:32.134 --> 27:34.004
(SCOFFS)

27:34.005 --> 27:37.611
We find in cases where there's
latent homosexuality...

27:37.612 --> 27:41.018
I am not a homosexual.

27:41.019 --> 27:42.621
I read your books.

27:42.622 --> 27:45.226
Men have impotence for
all sorts of reasons.

27:45.227 --> 27:46.830
Their parents are too strict,

27:46.831 --> 27:49.469
or they go to church too many times.

27:49.470 --> 27:51.138
Homosexuality is a bit different.

27:51.139 --> 27:55.714
How? I just want it out of my head.

27:55.715 --> 27:59.822
Just like all those
other suffering men.

27:59.823 --> 28:03.262
Have you never wanted to stop

28:03.263 --> 28:05.467
wanting what you want

28:05.468 --> 28:07.972
because you know it will
only cause you misery?

28:07.973 --> 28:10.979
That is all I am asking for.

28:19.963 --> 28:22.868
Oh. It's lovely here.

28:22.869 --> 28:25.072
Mm-hmm.

28:25.073 --> 28:28.078
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

28:28.079 --> 28:33.089
<i>♪♪♪</i>

28:34.325 --> 28:37.665
Oh, my.

28:37.666 --> 28:39.669
KELLER: Garden of Eden.

28:39.670 --> 28:44.680
<i>♪♪♪</i>

28:47.886 --> 28:49.522
Good afternoon.

28:49.523 --> 28:51.092
Happy fishing.

28:52.762 --> 28:54.932
Mr. Keller.

28:54.933 --> 28:56.937
Welcome to paradise.

29:04.653 --> 29:06.489
Virginia found out we did
the initial interview

29:06.490 --> 29:07.992
with the Clavermores.

29:07.993 --> 29:09.729
She pitched a fit to Masters

29:09.730 --> 29:11.699
and now it's very likely
we'll be taken off the case.

29:11.700 --> 29:12.935
Well, we knew that was a possibility.

29:12.936 --> 29:14.705
I'm sure that interview is on tape.

29:14.706 --> 29:16.241
And obviously, no one's heard it yet,

29:16.242 --> 29:17.711
